This week=E2=80=99s Stratechery Interview is with Benedict Evans ( https://=
www.threads.net/@benedictevans?hl=3Den ). Evans is an independent tech anal=
yst based in New York. Evans started his career in investment banking with =
a focus on the telecom sector, before his first stint as an independent ana=
lyst focused on mobile. In 2014 Evans joined Andreessen Horowitz as partner=
 and analyst, before departing in 2020. Evans was an inspiration for me whe=
n I started Stratechery, and it was a real delight to talk with him this we=
ek.

In this Interview we cover Evans=E2=80=99 career, before exploring the diff=
erences between European and American approaches to regulation. We cover an=
titrust questions, including the Apple case, and Evans explains why he=E2=
=80=99s not sure how much it matters. After that we focus on AI: what are t=
he right frameworks to think about AI=E2=80=99s impact, both on society and=
 on the largest tech companies? Is generative AI the end state, and will it=
 manifest as a generalizable assistant or as an ingredient in new generatio=
ns of products? Is there a bubble =E2=80=94 and what would it mean if it po=
ps? I thought this was a great conversation =E2=80=94 Evans=E2=80=99 has we=
ll thought-through frameworks for nearly everything =E2=80=94 and I trust y=
ou will enjoy listening to it as much as I enjoyed having it.

Evans=E2=80=99 website is located at ben-evans.com ( https://www.ben-evans.=
com/ ) , where he both posts long-form essays ( https://www.ben-evans.com/e=
ssays ) and hosts subscriptions for his newsletter ( https://www.ben-evans.=
com/newsletter ). Evans has written about many of the topics we discuss in =
this Interview; I will link to them as appropriate, but strongly suggest yo=
u subscribe.

